        <h1>Refurbishment work to improve Eastcote station</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        10 August 2005
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Refurbishment work to improve Eastcote station as part of Transport for London's five-year &pound;10bn investment programme will commence on Sunday 14 August, and will continue until mid-December 2005.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Eastcote station will close at 2100 from Sunday to Thursday while work is carried out
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            While this refurbishment work takes place, Eastcote station will close at 2100, Sunday to Thursday. 
<p>A replacement bus service will be in operation after 2100 between Rayners Lane and Ruislip stations.</p>
<p>The refurbishment works to be undertaken by Metronet Rail SSL will include the restoration of heritage features, the replacement of CCTV cameras, installation of customer Help Points, an enhanced public address system, new wall tiles, improved lighting and ceilings, and tactile strips on platforms and stairs, along with contrasting handrails.</p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call: 020 7222 1234 or visit TfL's website: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/">http://www.tfl.gov.uk/</a></p>
<p>
<hr>

<p>Live information on TfL's Realtime pages displays latest updates to London's transport modes, including the Tube, DLR, bus and Network Rail: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime">www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime</a> </p>
<p>Journey Planner checks the transport network's status before providing results. The best available route will be shown automatically: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner">www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner</a> </p>
<p>Travel alerts via SMS and email can be set up at: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts">www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts</a></p>

     

        
        
        
